We present a case report of a patient with glioblastoma multiforme (GBM) 
complicated by extracranial metastasis (ECM) whose survival of nearly four years 
surpassed the anticipated life expectancy given numerous negative prognostic 
factors including EGFRvIII-mutation, unmethylated MGMT promoter status, and ECM. 
